7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 843, L.D. 1268, “An Act to Address
10 Employee Recruitment and Retention Issues Within the Maine State Ferry Service by
11 Providing a Yearly Stipend”
12 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the enacting clause and inserting the
13 following:
14 'Sec. 1. 23 MRSA §4408 is enacted to read:
15 §4408. Stipend for employees
16 Beginning January 1, 2027, the Department of Transportation shall provide an annual
17 reliability performance stipend of $3,000 to all full-time state employees of the Maine State
18 Ferry Service. The employee must receive the stipend as a lump-sum payment by
19 December 1st of each year the employee qualifies for the stipend. For the purposes of this
20 section, "reliability performance stipend" means a stipend paid to a full-time state employee
21 of the Maine State Ferry Service when the Maine State Ferry Service achieves 99% of
22 schedule reliability for all scheduled Maine State Ferry Service operations from November
23 1st to October 31st. The stipend is not affected by scheduled operations canceled due to
24 weather. Tolls under section 4404 may not be increased to cover the cost of stipends under
25 this section.
26 Sec. 2. Transfer from the Highway Fund unallocated surplus; Department
27 of Transportation, Multimodal-Island Ferry Service. Notwithstanding any
28 provision of law to the contrary, on or before December 1, 2027, and every December 1st
29 thereafter, the State Controller shall transfer $450,000 from the unallocated surplus of the
30 Highway Fund to the Department of Transportation, Multimodal-Island Ferry Service
31 program, enterprise account for providing annual stipends to qualified employees of the
32 Maine State Ferry Service.'
33 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
34 number to read consecutively.
